comments.comment:
I use java and have the same problem with you. Thank you very much for tipping.

Depending on my expierence on AJAX, only setting <code>'no-cache'</code> may not affect SILLY IE. So I add a timestamp to the XML:

<pre class="java"><code>response.setContentType("text/xml; charset=UTF-8");
response.setHeader("Cache-Control", "no-cache");
PrintWriter out = response.getWriter();
out.println("<r>"+Calendar.getInstance().getTime().getTime()+"</r>");
out.flush();
out.close();</code></pre>

Now it works fine!! Thank you again guys!
